<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="ObjectMethod_login_query_twiki"></a> <a href="/bin/view/TWiki/ObjectMethod" class="twikiLink">ObjectMethod</a> <strong>login</strong> <tt>($query,$twiki)</tt> </span></h2>
<p />
this allows the login and logon cgi-scripts to use the same code. 
all a logon does, is re-direct to viewauth, and apache then figures out 
if it needs to challenge the user
<p />
<p />
